description:
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute Trusts in the UK – and with more than 20,000 employees – Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust (MFT) is on an exciting mission to deliver high-quality care to the people of Manchester, Trafford and beyond. Our vision is to create and deliver a seamless 24/7 service that extends beyond excellent care within our nine hospitals and community services within our Local Care Organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be to lead on the separation, transition and integration of compliance, risk and governance and support the hospital redevelopment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the Deputy Director of Facilities and Group Head of Compliance to ensure that the FM services to the whole of the MFT estate are provided in a compliant fashion, with all known risks recorded and appropriately managed; and that the Trust structure is statutorily compliant. Reporting to the Deputy Director of Facilities / Group Head of Compliance, provide processes, structures and procedures for the site-based Compliance Teams to ensure that the FM services (primarily Hard FM and decontamination services) are provided by the in-house teams and other FM service providers in a compliant manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the development of compliance-based services in line with Department of Health strategy and guidelines and liaise with the Trust’s Property &amp; Estate Development team to ensure that development schemes and life-cycle replacement of the estate are carried out in a compliant fashion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTBC&lt;/p&gt;
